		nil,
		nil
	},
	[29693] = {
		"The General's Edge",
		"As you gradually gather your senses and begin to take in your surroundings, this object stands out amongst the strewn wreckage.\n\nIt occurs to you that this is the first time you've seen Nazgrim's axe outside of his tight grasp. Somehow, this fact makes your predicament even more unsettling...\n\nYou know that dead or alive, the General would want his weapon back in his possession.",
		"Bring Nazgrim's axe to General Nazgrim.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[29696] = {
		"My Stars!",
		"A number of Kiryn's articles have been scattered around the area by wood sprites, but this one stands out as important to you.\n\nThe bag once hung from her waist, loaded with throwing stars. Without them, her arsenal will be considerably diminished.\n\nIf you were to retrieve the weapons from the pests that inhabit this region, it could only help your cause.",
		"Collect 100 of Kiryn's Throwing Stars from Devious Wood Sprites.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[29712] = {
		"Horde Justice",
		"Your mind races as you struggle to come to terms with your predicament - shipwrecked on an uncharted land, nearly all of the crew lost....\n\nAs you look at the corpse of this unfortunate creature you realize that the area is crawling with his kind, and that they're pillaging whatever supplies haven't been destroyed.\n\nIt's time to introduce these vermin to some good old-fashioned Horde justice.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[29713] = {
		"Standard Protocol",
		"The Sky Shark has been totally destroyed.\n\nWith Alliance forces about, standard protocol requires the destruction of any sensitive technologies. These solenoids most certainly fall under that category.\n\nThe Horde's directives are clear, round up the solenoids for destruction.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[29714] = {
		"Wet Work!",
		"If any Alliance naval forces have come ashore, the smoky fires from your crash will lead them right to you and what remains of your crew.\n\nThere must be a way to extinguish those flames...\n\nThis barrel seems to have survived the catastrophe intact. Perhaps it's still water-tight.\n\nOnly one way to find out!",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[29715] = {
		"The Witch in the Woods",
		"Oh please $r!  Can you help me?\n\nSome of the village children were playing in the woods and haven't come back. Could you please keep an eye out for them if you are going out there?\n\nI told those village rascals to leave that old widow up in the woods alone. My guess is they are probably harassing her. They think she is a witch.",
		"Find An Windfur on the road north of the Jade Witch Hut.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		"Find An Windfur.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[29717] = {
		"Додолу, кицю!",
		"Я намагалася битися з одним із нефритових тигрів у лісі, але вони були занадто страшні. Вони дивляться на тебе, і ти перетворюєшся на нефритову статую!\n\nЧиста правда! Ні, подруга сестри Чень, почула це від мами Кая.\n\nЯ хочу бути хороброю, як ти. Можеш показати мені, як побити тих нефритових тигрів?",
		"Знищте 8 нефритових вартових.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		"Ого! А ти {sex|міцний|міцна}!",
		nil
	},
	[29718] = {
		"Sixteen Fluid Ounces of Prevention",
		"Better safe than sorry.\n\nThe pillars of smoke surrounding the crash site will be a beacon to any Alliance who might have seen your Zeppelin in distress.\n\nUntil you and your depleted crew get your bearings, you could do without that kind of trouble.\n\nExtinguishing the wreckage fires is just plain common sense.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[29720] = {
		"The Jade Witch",
		"The Jade Witch must still have Shin.\n\nI... I can't do it!  I don't want to see the witch.  Can you please go talk to her?  You're an adult.  I don't think she would turn you into jade.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[29722] = {
		"A Lesson in Bravery",
		"Can you help teach me to be brave like you?\n\nWhen we played our prank on the witch we made a bunch of Leafy Tricksters angry.  I think the witch did something to them.\n\nCan you show me how you stand up to them?",
		"Defeat 8 Leafy Tricksters south of the Jade Witch Hut.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[29724] = {
		"Burial at Sea",
		"These savages are... ruthless.\n\nThey've dragged off our dying soldiers to be tormented in their camps. This is no way for our valiant brothers to die.\n\nI shall join them soon enough, {class}. Please, put my mind at ease and their bodies to rest.\n\nFind their remains at the camps surrounding the wreckage. Put them out of the reach of these creatures.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[29728] = {
		"Explosive Evidence",
		"I must ask you to do one more thing for me, $n.\n\nThe personal effects on this ship cannot be left for others to find. We'll have to destroy it.\n\nI cobbled together some Makeshift Dynamite from the scraps you brought me.\n\nPlace the dynamite anywhere on the ship, but take care not to put them too close together.\n\nThey might be...uh...a little unwieldy, so you should spread them out in case of premature detonation.",
		"Plant 4 Makeshift Dynamite near the sunken ship at Sapphire's End. Makeshift Dynamite must be placed at least 10 yards apart.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[29729] = {
		"Without a Trace",
		"The explosives are set. All we have to do now is pull the trigger.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[29732] = {
		"What Goes Down, Must Come Up!",
		"Rivett left behind what looks to be an important piece of equipment. Along its shaft you are able to make out the words: Goblin Drone Dispenser.\n\nWith a simple calibration, the device is set to deliver drones to Nazgrim's basecamp.\n\nEasy enough....\n\nThere's just one problem. The only supply crates worth transporting have fallen to the cliff ledge below the crash impact.\n\nAs you ponder the issue, you see the long, coiled tail of a Cliff Glider fly by the corner of your eye...",
		"Use the Goblin Drone Dispenser near the Exposed Root to recover supplies.\n\nNOTE: Each use will require one Cliff Glider Tail.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[29744] = {
		"Some \"Pupil of Nature\"",
		"Wood sprites are not prone to wandering, so I'm surprised they ventured down as far as the mason's quarter. Something must be forcing them out of their natural habitat.\n\nThese particular sprites are native to the Woods of the Lost, just north of here. I'd go myself, but I've heard those woods are haunted.\n\nSo yeah, that's out.\n\nI guess we'll never know.\n\n<Weng coughs.>\n\nOrrrr... A big brave adventurer like YOU could go check it out! What do you say?",
		"Investigate the Woods of the Lost, northeast of the Greenstone Quarry.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[29766] = {
		"A Good Start",
		"Regardless of our predicament, our orders stand. We are to learn the lay of this land and prepare it for Hellscream's fleet.\n\nBut first, we must deal with these savages!\n\nYou see these corpses I've stacked up around the camp? I want mountains of them!\n\nWe are the Horde!\n\nThese vermin have not learned to fear us yet, but we will fix that soon enough...",
		"Kill 4 Hozen Mudflingers, 4 Hozen Skullthumpers, and 3 Hozen Fishcatchers.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[29773] = {
		"Wugou, the Spirit of Earth",
		"$n! Well, the plus side is that finding Wugou was easy enough. Waking him... not so much. I think he's going to wake quite sore from all the pushing and hitting I've done trying to rouse him.\n\nAre you a deep sleeper at all, $n? What wakes you up in the morning?\n\nRolling out of bed always seems to do it for me, so I figure let's just go for that! I tied off some ropes to the ox cart. We send it running and give him a good roll, and we should be good! Care to give the ox a good slap to get it going?",
		"Slap the ox.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		"Return to Ji Firepaw in the Dai-Lo Farmstead.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[29837] = {
		"Sacred Scroll",
		"The unfamiliar markings on this parchment have an elegance about them that Yoggtord and his gang don't seem capable of.\n\nYou suspect that, like everything else these Hozu possess, this is stolen merchandise.\n\nPerhaps the original owner of the scroll is still nearby...",
		"Bring the Illegible Scroll to Lorewalker Cho.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[29841] = {
		"Lay of the Land[TEMP]",
		"Grah!!\n\nFor every one of these muck-flingers we kill, another two spring from the woods to take its place. I wouldn't share this with the others, but it's clear that we won't last long here, $n.\n\nI must stay and defend what remains of our belongings. You scout out the region and seek a solution to our primate problem.\n\nGo now. Our hope goes with you...",
		"Explore the region.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[29842] = {
		"Seeking Answers",
		"<Cho endures your stream of questions before speaking.>\n\nSo much to ponder, traveler...\n\nYou first must learn how to ask before your mind can discern the truth.\n\nI have completed my meditations for today, but my candles remain at the Cairn of Blood.\n\nGo there. Clear your mind. We will speak again when you are prepared to hear my words.",
		"Use the candles to meditate at the Cairn of Blood.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[29856] = {
		"Cairn of Bone",
		"Your mind felt clear.\n\nYou thought you were focused.\n\nMaybe it was the droning of the nearby insects that put you to sleep. That must've been it!\n\nOut of the corner of your eye, you see another of the stone formations just north of here.\n\nPerhaps it's quieter at that one...",
		"Use the Meditation Candle at the Cairn of Bone.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[29858] = {
		"Wisdom of the Ages",
		"You must learn to approach your life's trials with humility and an open mind, stranger.\n\nWisdom cannot fit through the narrow slits of the skeptic's eye.\n\nMeet me at the Cairn of Stone and I shall teach you the ancient art of meditation.\n\nOnce you are at peace, you may find that the answers you seek are not as distant as you might think them to be.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[29869] = {
		"One Hand Clapping",
		"You have much yet to learn, but your feet are now on the path to enlightenment.\n\nTake what I have taught you here and apply it at the lake to the west.\n\nWith patience and practice, harmony and enlightenment can be attained. Then, wisdom will flow freely into your mind.\n\nAlso, you will be far enough away that your snoring will not interfere with my own studies.\n\nFarewell, stranger.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[29878] = {
		"Building a Better Hozen Trap",
		"One thing is now painfully clear. The Hozen love their 'slickies'.\n\nWhile deep in your meditative trance, scattered images and impressions came to your mind. Now fully awake, you struggle to make sense of the experience.\n\nThe beginnings of an absurd plan begin to take shape in your head. It might just be crazy enough to work...",
		"Collect 8 Slickies and 8 Intact Pottery Jars from Lake Kittitata.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[29880] = {
		"Catch and Release!",
		"As you place one fish in each jar, your optimism grows.\n\nThis just might work! Ideally, rescuing the Hozen from your makeshift trap will soften their stance towards you.\n\nTime to set some bait.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[29886] = {
		"Zen Healing",
		"Your friend Taylor is in critical shape. Unfortunately, his wounds are tainted by hozen poison, which is very difficult to cure.\n\nLuckily, through many generations of fighting the hozen, my people have developed medicines to treat such injuries.\n\nThe flowers growing on the surface of Glass Lake are needed to make the antidote.\n\n$n, go quickly and bring back some blooms. Your Admiral's life depends on it.",
		"Collect 6 Zen Lotus.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		"Return to Mishka at Pearlfin Village in the Jade Forest.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[29895] = {
		"Trail of the White Pawn",
		"Although the cloak is ragged and torn, there is no mistaking the fine tailoring and the King's royal crest.\n\nYou should show it to your Alliance commander.",
		"Show the cloak to Admiral Taylor at Pearlfin Village in the Jade Forest.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[29938] = {
		"Friends and Foes",
		"These ookin' Jinyu grookin Kah Kah's nephews!\n\nWikket once kill many hozen. Now wikket kill many jinyu.",
		"Kill 7 Riverstride Jinyu at the Slicky Stream.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30003] = {
		"A Book By Its Cover",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30190] = {
		"Sprite Plight",
		"Sprites again! I hate these things. We need to stop them before they hurt someone or burn down half of the village!\n\nIf you see any of the pests, please deal with them! ",
		"Kill 8 Slateskin Troublemakers.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30191] = {
		"Steer Clear of the Beer Here",
		"Someone left some beer out up on the southern rise and now the sprites have developed a taste for our brew. They've been sneaking into town all morning, stealing whatever kegs they find.\n\nBring back what you can. A pandaren worker without brew is just... it won't be very productive. We need the men in good spirits.",
		"Recover 10 Stolen Mistfall Kegs.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		"Return to Mayor Shiyo at Mistfall Village in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30192] = {
		"My Town, It's on Fire",
		"I don't know if you noticed, but my town is burning...\n\nThe sprites have started kicking the braziers! They're going to set fire to the whole town!\n\nPlease help us! Stamp out any fires you see!",
		"Put out 30 Brazier Fires.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30193] = {
		"Meating Expectations",
		"Hard workers deserve hearty meals, but I'm all out of good meat!\n\nCan you head out into the forest and get me some fresh gazelle meat?",
		"Retrieve 10 slabs of Fairlands Gazelle Meat.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30194] = {
		"Encroaching Storm",
		"The villagers have lost another yak this morning to one of the thundermaw wolves from across the river. The wolves grow bold.\n\nThis is a sign that they are breeding beyond the vale's ability to sustain them. It's time to thin their numbers again.\n\nIf you are willing to aid me in this, you would have my sincere appreciation.",
		"Kill 8 Thundermaw Wolves.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30195] = {
		"Blooming Blossoms",
		"Would you do a humble merchant a favor? I've been needin' to refresh my stock of eternal blossoms. They grow in the woods nearby.\n\nCould you help me out, perhaps?",
		"Collect 10 Eternal Blossoms.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30196] = {
		"Lushroom Rush",
		"Building a new village makes for hungry workers it seems!\n\nI have a hearty stew recipe prepared, but I need some lushrooms from the Tu Shen Burial Ground to the east. Apparently there are roused spirits causing trouble up there though, and I'm not very well suited for the violent life.\n\nIf you're heading up the burial grounds today, could you collect some lushrooms for me?",
		"Collect 12 Lushrooms.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		"Return to Cooke Tope at Mistfall Village in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30200] = {
		"In Ashen Webs",
		"We used to have the trainees clear out the ruins of spiders as part of their training, but now we send them straight to the mogu front. The spiders have gotten out of control.\n\nCare to put things back in control?",
		"Kill 8 Ashweb Spiders.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30204] = {
		"That's Not a Rock!",
		"Okay, these spiders are seriously creeping me out. Especially those egg sacs they leave lying around that I keep accidentally stepping on only to be covered in very little but very creepy spiderlings. Ug, makes me shudder just thinking about it.\n\nI say you burn them. Burn them all.",
		"Kill 50 Ashweb Spiderlings. Use Kun's torch to burn them inside their pods.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30205] = {
		"Runelocked",
		"Hello, friend.\n\nOne of Leven's men brought word to me of a mogu artifact in the eastern ruins, but said he couldn't figure out how to retrieve it. I suspect it's guarded by one of their rune locks.\n\nIf you go to the artifact, you should find four runes somewhere nearby that when activated will release the lock. If you could bring the artifact back to me, I would be very grateful.",
		"Retrieve the Ancient Mogu Artifact.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30206] = {
		"Runes in the Ruins",
		"In the walls of the ruins themselves, there are precious runestones that we can make use of back in the eastern vale.\n\nIf you see any while you are within the ruins, would you be so kind as to bring them back to me?",
		"Collect 12 Guo-Lai Runestones.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30225] = {
		"The Ashweb Matriarch",
		"My dear Kun spotted more spiders pouring out of the Guo-Lai Halls this morning, and when he went to investigate, he uncovered another spider matriarch inside.\n\nI need you to kill it.",
		"Kill Bloodtip, the Ashweb Matriarch.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		"Return to Anji Autumnlight at the Ruins of Guo-Lai in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30226] = {
		"Blood on the Rise",
		"A small group of mogu have been sighted on Ruin's Rise, to the north.\n\nExtinguish them.",
		"Kill 8 Shao-Tien mogu on Ruin's Rise.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30227] = {
		"Wulon, the Granite Sentinel",
		"One of the quilen statues in Guo-Lai Halls came to life and nearly killed my precious Kun. I won't have it! No one threatens my Kun.\n\nI want you to go in there and smash the thing to pieces. I'd do it myself, but I need to attend to my lover's wounds first.",
		"Kill Wulon, the Granite Sentinel.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		"Return to Anji Autumnlight at the Ruins of Guo-Lai in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30228] = {
		"Troubling the Troublemakers",
		"The wood sprites are back. I need you to kill them before they cause anymore trouble.",
		"Kill 8 Stonebark sprites.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30231] = {
		"Pomfruit Pickup",
		"I need more pomfruit! Go knock some loose from the trees for me, would you?\n\nTake this, I use it when I go harvesting. Things go quicker when the fruit comes to you!",
		"Gather 12 Pomfruit.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30232] = {
		"Ruffling Some Feathers",
		"The hawk numbers in the vale are thriving. This is opportune for our fletchers, for we will need a great number of feathers if we are to keep the archers upon the wall stocked with arrows.\n\nIf you would not mind, could you aid us in gathering these feathers?",
		"Gather 80 Silken Feathers.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30233] = {
		"Cracklefang",
		"Hi! So, I have a dilemma. I've only got one good wolf name.... wait for it... Cracklefang! I know, amazing right?! But now there are TWO big nasty wolves in the forest, which is all kinds of confusing.\n\nI need you to kill one of them so I can free up the name. Should be simple enough, yeah? Especially for someone of your incredibleness.\n\nSo, are you on board? I'm hoping for yes!",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30234] = {
		"Vicejaw",
		"Vicejaw! Sounds absolutely violent, does it not? I came up with it myself, and I think it's very suiting. I tried to wrestle my staff away from him for hours, but he simply would not let go!\n\nOkay, it was really more like a few seconds. I like to be truthful to my friends, even if it makes my stories significantly more boring.\n\nAnyway, would you be so kind as to release your oh-so-potent wrath upon this crocolisk with a vice-like jaw, and then kindly bring my staff back? Preferably in-tact!",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30235] = {
		"Quid Pro Quo",
		"Quid is a very powerful and very ancient water spirit, though you might not know it with his child-like ways.\n\nThis morning, Quid nearly killed several villagers in the bar when he jokingly caused several of the water kegs to explode.\n\nAs long as the water flows, Quid will remain. He cannot be slain. But he can be reminded that we do not take his dangerous antics in jest.\n\nWould you be willing to carry this message to him on behalf of the village?",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30236] = {
		"Aetha",
		"It seems Aetha has been levitating the livestock and dropping them into the river again. The mayor has requested that we remind her that these kinds of jokes are not welcomed.\n\nWould you be so generous as to travel to the ridge above the village and teach her this lesson? You cannot kill her, you can only send her away for a time, but this should prove a potent reminder.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30237] = {
		"The Pandaren Uprising Relived",
		"In the Tu Shen Burial Ground to the east, the spirits of ancient mogu are locked in battle with the spirits of our pandaren ancestors that rose up against them. The spirits have seen no rest since the return of the mogu to the valley.\n\nIf you would be willing to go to the graveyard and force the mogu to relive their defeat again, we might offer some lasting peace to the spirits of our ancestors.",
		"Kill 8 Ancient Mogu Spirits.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		"Return to Che Wildwalker at Mistfall Village in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30238] = {
		"Return to Rest",
		"The spirits of our ancestors are reliving one of the most revered battles in our history at the Tu Shen Burial Grounds to the east.\n\nDo as I ask, {race}, and honor their gravestones. Remind them that they are respected even these many years later, and that they are deserving of peaceful rest.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30239] = {
		"Lao-Fe the Slavebinder",
		"You can hear the spirit of Lao-Fe, the Slavebinder shouting taunts from the cave at the top of Tu Shen Burial Mound.\n\nDefeating him will surely serve to ensure victory for the spirits of the pandaren monks.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30244] = {
		"Along the Serpent's Spine",
		"There are mantid on top of the wall. The defenders on the ramparts are calling for help!",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30245] = {
		"Lost Scouts",
		"We sent some scouts towards the Five Sisters to the north to try and find whatever mogu leader has risen up to direct their movements in the valley. Few have returned.\n\nI'd like to think they're just off downing too much ale or being irresponsible with some young pandaren, but they may actually be in some trouble.\n\nCan you scout for the scouts? And see if they've turned up any information on that leader while you're at it?",
		"Recover 3 Shado-Pan Scout reports.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30246] = {
		"Upon the Ramparts",
		"Some of the mantid have made it on top of the wall. There's some risk they'll route the soldiers we have posted there if their numbers are large enough.\n\nI need you to get on top of the wall and help clear out any that have broken through.",
		"Kill 10 Krik'thik mantid on top of the Gate of the Setting Sun.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30248] = {
		"The Butcher",
		"Scouts reports place the displaced Shao-Tien Imperion at the north end of the wall.\n\nAngi Autumnlight spelled out your goal in no uncertain terms: find this leader and kill him.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30249] = {
		"Under the Setting Sun",
		"A giant beast has burrowed under the gate into the courtyard. The defenders need your help!",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30251] = {
		"Vyraxxis, the Krik'thik Swarm-Lord",
		"A giant mantid is terrorizing the inside of the wall. It seems doubtful that the defenders will be able deal with it without you.",
		"Kill Vyraxxis, the Krik'thik Swarm-Lord.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30263] = {
		"Clearing in the Forest",
		"The Shao-Tien are on their heels. Most of them retreated to Winterbough Glade after their last defeat. We should press the advantage.\n\nTake the fight to these mogu in the clearing to the northwest. Let us leave them no minute of rest as long as they remain in the Vale.",
		"Kill 6 Shao-Tien mogu in Winterbough Glade.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30264] = {
		"Enemy at the Gates",
		"The mantid forces are pouring against the wall. I've arranged for some flying serpents to cut away at their forces from the air.\n\nWould you be willing to take the reigns on one of them?",
		"Use a Shado-Pan Sky Serpent to kill 60 Krik'thik attackers, 3 Krik'thik War Wagons, and 3 Krik'thik Catapults.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30265] = {
		"Sparkle in the Eye",
		"I've been staring down into the waters of the lake, pondering life, love, and everything beautiful, and suddenly I realized that the sparkles in the water aren't just a reflection of my radiant personality, there are actually some sort of shining objects down there! Surely valuable.\n\nWould you mind taking a drip and relieving the lake's depths of its mysterious sparkles? Pretty please?",
		"Recover 8 Shining Rubies.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30281] = {
		"The Silent Approach",
		"<He leans over and draws a picture of what can only be a mogu, points towards the lake to the west, drags the blunt side of his dagger across his throat, and looks at you expectantly. It seems he wants you to kill mogu at Whitepetal Lake.>",
		"Kill 6 Shao-Tien mogu at Whitepetal Lake.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30282] = {
		"Burning Away the Filth",
		"The mogu have erected their filthy banners around the lake to the west, claiming it as their own. Take this torch and show them what we think of their banners.",
		"Burn 10 Shao-Tien Banners.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30283] = {
		"A Smashing Impression",
		"Sometimes I feel sorry for these mogu... maybe ripping out the spirits of other races is just their way of coping with family issues at home? Maybe we should be more sympathetic to where all this aggression stems from?\n\nOr we could just smash all their soul-stealing ritual objects down at the lake. That sounds more fun to me personally.",
		"Destroy the Shao-Tien Ritual Statues.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30284] = {
		"A Thousand Pointy Teeth",
		"The water has been frothing with danger this day! Some sort of swarming, meat-eating fishy nastiness has taken up residence in our lake! Deplorable. And just when I was considering stripping down to my nothings to take a mid-day dip!\n\nYou are adept in the ways of slaughtering any manner of nasty, are you not? Would you put your skills to use this day, in the name of pandaren everywhere desiring a swim?\n\nIt's a truly noble cause, especially with me among their ranks!",
		"Kill 9 Knifetooth Swarmers.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		"Return to Ren Firetongue at Whitepetal Lake in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30285] = {
		"Wu Kao Scouting Reports",
		"There were some scouting reports unaccounted for after the attack. If we're lucky, they're still out in the village, but the mogu may have gotten their hands on some of them as well.\n\nIf you could bring back any scouting reports you find, it would definitely put my mind at ease. We can't afford to let the mogu in on our positions or any of the artifacts we've found, lest the men be in even more danger than they already are.",
		"Recover 3 Wu Kao Scouting Reports.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		"Return to Sun Tenderheart at Mistfall Village in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30286] = {
		"Backed Into a Corner",
		"Many villagers are cornered and scared, unable to defend themselves. You will need to defend them. Rescue them.\n\nGo quickly friend, save as many as you can!",
		"Rescue 6 Cornered Mistfall Villagers.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		"Return to Sun Tenderheart at Mistfall Village in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30287] = {
		"Mogu Make Poor House Guests",
		"Leven sent Rook here to stop mogu, but there are more than Rook can kill alone.\n\nYou help?  Rook will tell Leven you helped.  Promise.",
		"Kill 6 Shado-Tien attackers in Mistfall Village.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		"Return to Rook Stonetoe at Mistfall Village in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30288] = {
		"My Town, It's On Fire Again",
		"I don't know if you noticed, but my town is on fire... again.\n\nWe have water buckets all over town, but no one can get out to put out the fires. Please, please, help us!",
		"Use Mistfall Water Buckets to douse 60 fires.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		"Return to Mayor Shiyo at Mistfall Village in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30289] = {
		"Freeing Mind and Body",
		"Mogu stealing peoples minds! Making them do evil things.\n\nDon't kill them, just kill the mogu, then they forget about all the mogu mind stealing and stop being evil. You should fix people like Rook is.",
		"Free 6 Dominated Guards by killing their controllers.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		"Return to Rook Stonetoe at Mistfall Village in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30290] = {
		"Stonebound Killers",
		"Mogu stone dog creatures chasing villagers and hurting them. Rook try to smash some, but they too fast.\n\nYou help smash some too?",
		"Kill 8 Stonebound Quilen.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		"Return to Rook Stonetoe at Mistfall Village in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30291] = {
		"Stunning Display",
		"I've been talking to Tantan here... again... and he insists that fishing is some kind of fabulous. I was skeptical, but I gave it another go. I'm not a big fan of that whole holding a stick and waiting method though, so I tried something a bit more direct.\n\nWould you be a doll and go collect any of the still intact fish floating belly up in the lake for me?",
		"Collect 12 Stunned Whitepetal Carp.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30292] = {
		"Rude Awakenings",
		"The mogu are taking over the minds of the saurok at the lake to our west and turning them against us! The thing is, they were already against us, so I'm not sure they really thought this thing through fully.\n\nAnyway, Anji's the fighter in this pair, I'm more the lover, so I'm looking for someone to do all the weapon swinging and spell flinging and war crying and such.\n\nCan you go kill some saurok for me?",
		"Kill 8 Dominated Paleblade Flesheaters.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30293] = {
		"In Enemy Hands",
		"The Shao-Tien Mindbenders have taken over the minds of our defenders down at Whitepetal Lake to the west. Get down there and kill the mogu that are controlling them, but don't kill the defenders! Killing their captors should free them from their mind control.\n\nSooner would be better. Anji might try to go down there to help soon, and her ability to restrain herself when in the heat of things is not one of the qualities I married her for.",
		"Beat 8 Possessed Whitepetal Defenders until they're freed of mogu possession.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		"Return to Autumnlight at the Golden Pagoda in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30296] = {
		"Gaohun the Soul-Severer",
		"Big mogu leader is here! Up behind village. If we kill big mogu leader, Leven be happy with us for sure!\n\nYou been good at helping Rook. Want to help more maybe? Please?",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30297] = {
		"Baolai the Immolator",
		"Big mogu leader is here! Up behind village. If we kill big mogu leader, Leven be happy with us for sure!\n\nYou been good at helping Rook. Want to help more maybe? Please?",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30298] = {
		"Painting the Ruins Red",
		"The mogu think they can inhabit these ruins uncontested. Let's show them the error in their ways.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30299] = {
		"No Stone Unturned",
		"The mogu have forced spirits into their old statues to bring them to life, control them, and turn them against us.\n\nThe only way to free the bound spirits is to destroy their vessels.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30300] = {
		"The Key to Success",
		"The mogu have taken prisoners. They'll be tortured or worse.\n\nFind any way you can to free them from their cages.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30301] = {
		"Offering a Warm Welcome",
		"There is no more sure message we can send them then to burn the tents the sleep in.\n\nScour the ruins. Destroy every tent you find.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30302] = {
		"The Imperion Threat",
		"Scouts spotted a Shao-Tien Imperion entering the Guo-Lai Halls. I need someone I can trust to make sure he doesn't come out of there alive.\n\nI think you're the {class} for the job.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30304] = {
		"Hard as a Rock",
		"Hey! You know what awesome thing happened to me this morning?\n\nI was strolling through the ruins with Anji, eyes on the ground so I wouldn't step on anymore of those creepy spider pods, when one of the statues came to life and tried to smash me!\n\nAnji ended up doing the smashing. But I'm not satisfied. I think that you should go out there and smash all the statues, whether they're moving or not. It's the only way to be sure.",
		"Destroy 10 Mogu Statues.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30305] = {
		"He Knows What He's Doing",
		"You know He Softfoot? Sneaky guy, don't talk much. He put traps all over ruins for mogu. He said Rook just need to trick mogu into traps. Rook don't really know how.\n\nMaybe you do it? You find traps, you get bad guys into traps? Can you not tell He though, please?",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30307] = {
		"The Eternal Vigil",
		"Good to have you with us, $c. If you're joining the fight, I need more men out up at the Golden Stair to clear out the mogu setting up base there.\n\nCan I count on you?",
		"Kill 8 Shao-Tien mogu on the Golden Terrace.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30308] = {
		"Stone Hard Quilen",
		"Leven always says the only good quilen is a dead quilen, and I'm inclined to agree. You here to aid the cause?",
		"Kill 6 Granite Quilen.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30309] = {
		"Set in Stone",
		"The mogu have been sending their narcissistic stone effigies onto our battlefield today. They're brining them to life up on the Golden Stair.\n\nThe bigger they are, the harder we hit'm. You in?",
		"Destroy 6 Mogu Effigies.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30310] = {
		"Thundering Skies",
		"The mogu have bent the will of sky serpents and turned them against us.\n\nThe defenders won't fare well against them, but you would. Head northwest towards the Golden Stair and remove them from the sky.",
		"Kill 3 Subjugated Serpents.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30312] = {
		"Given a Second Chance",
		"A foolish contingent attempted to mount an offensive on the Golden Stair through the eastern pass, and were bombarded by cannons. Those that made it back are in bad shape, and there are still wounded out in the field.\n\nHere are some bandages. Use these, or any other healing skills you possess, and help get our wounded defenders back to safety.\n\nPlease hurry, there is little time.",
		"Heal 6 Wounded Defenders.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30313] = {
		"The Moving Mists",
		"<He looks down at the dead fog creature at his feet, looks up at you, then points out into the mists surrounding the lake. It seems he wants you to find and kill more of these fog creatures.>",
		"Kill 8 Fog Walkers.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30314] = {
		"The Displaced Paleblade",
		"<He looks down at the dead saurok at his feet, looks up at you, then points out down the lake shore. It seems he wants you to find and kill more of these saurok.>",
		"Kill 8 Paleblade Saurok.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30320] = {
		"Free Spirits",
		"I came upon one of the Shao-Tien Soul-Render's daggers. It radiates a strong magic. I've been told it should allow you to enter their spirit vortexes.\n\nThe mogu use these to harvest spirits and bind them to their will, but I'm hoping you can use it to free the spirits.\n\nEnter any of the spirit vortexes you can find up on the Golden Stair, and free all the captive spirits you find.",
		"Enter Spirit Vortexes and free 15 pandaren spirits inside.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30338] = {
		"A Weighty Task",
		"For the life of me, I can't figure out why the mogu would have built all their statues and such down in that lake. I'm sure there wasn't always water down there, but it still seems wickedly inconvenient should it ever have rained.\n\nAh well, who's to fathom the strange intentions of the mogu...\n\nWould you be so kind as to swim down there and bring back any artifacts that seem even vaguely carry-able? I'd certainly appreciate it.",
		"Recover 8 Mogu Artifacts.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30339] = {
		"Getting your Hands Dirty",
		"Some of the best fishin' in all of pandaria in this lake right here. I brought enough brew to last me all day, but I didn't think to bring any bait.\n\nWho can really remember such things?\n\nIf you'd be willing to gather me some bait along the shore, I'd be willin' to think on you favorably when it comes time to price my merchandise. Oh, and I'll pay you too, of course. \n\nHow's that sound?",
		"Gather 12 Fresh Whitepetal Worms.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30340] = {
		"Stick in the Mud",
		"I came out for a beautiful day of fishin', but I didn't think to bring a pole. There are so many things to remember for fishin', I just can't keep it all in my head.\n\nThose reeds along the river look alright for makin' a pole out of. If you'd gather me some number of them, I'd be willin' to think on you favorably when it comes time to price my merchandise. Oh, and I'll pay you too, of course. \n\nHow's that sound?",
		"Gather 12 Whitepetal Reeds.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30341] = {
		"Under Watchful Eyes",
		"<He looks down at the dead mogu scout at his feet, looks up at you, then points out out down the lake shore. It seems he wants you to find and kill more of these mogu scouts.>",
		"Kill 8 Shao-Tien Surveyors.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30342] = {
		"Fiery Tongue, Fragile Feet",
		"I was kicking the water for fun again when one of those vicious crocolisks lunged out to try to bite my foot off! Rude! I have proceeded to rest my weary soles a few feet farther from the water, but I already look back on my water-kicking days longingly.\n\nWould you be so kind as to kill a crocolisk or eight for me? I assure you they deserve it for frightening me though.",
		"Kill 6 Stillwater Crocolisks.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30385] = {
		"Setting Sun Garrison",
		"I offer you my heartfelt appreciation for your aid. Anji awaits you in the Setting Sun Garrison to the west.\n\nMay the day favor you, young $c.",
		"Speak to Anji Autumnlight at the Setting Sun Garrison.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30442] = {
		"Blanche's Boomer Brew",
		"Brew Blanche's Boomer Brew by Protecting the Brewkegs.",
		"Help create the Boomer Brew. If the Brewkegs catch on fire, fix them!",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30444] = {
		"No Reprieve",
		"We've been granted a brief respite from the mogu attacks as they attempt to recoup near the Five Sisters to our north. I would like you to see to it that they not be granted a similar reprieve.\n\nShow no mercy.",
		"Kill 8 Shao-Tien mogu near the Five Sisters.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30458] = {
		"The Scouts Return",
		"$n, your friends have returned from their scouting mission. They need to see you immediately.\n\nI'm afraid...\n\nWell, I'd better say no more. You will see for yourself.",
		"Speak to Rell Nightwind at the Glassfin Village in the Jade Forest.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30481] = {
		"Carved in Stone",
		"You see the shiny stones in the walls? Rook wants some. The mogu been collecting them, so they have some to take too maybe.\n\nIf you find stones, you please bring them to Rook? Rook will be your friend.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30482] = {
		"The Soul-Gatherer",
		"A single large mogu performing a ritual on the lake caught your attention while you were killing the other mogu in the area. It seems unwise to let his ritual complete.",
		"Kill Shadowmaster Sydow and recover the beads from his corpse.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30630] = {
		"Into the Vale",
		"Ah, I have been waiting for your arrival, traveler.\n\nI wish we could meet in better times, but alas, I fear the situation in the Vale is quite dire.\n\nBut let us not speak of that now. Go visit Matron Vi Vinh at the Shrine of Seven Stars.\n\nShe should be able to settle you in.",
		"Speak to Matron Vi Vinh at the Shrine of Seven Stars in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30631] = {
		"The Shrine of Seven Stars",
		"Look at this creature, traveler. Only moments after we arrived, this mogu assassin attacked with no warning.\n\nHis blade was intended for the leader of the Golden Lotus. It is very lucky indeed that we were here to stop the attack.\n\nSeeing this attempt on Zhi's life, I fear for the safety of those who have already entered the valley.\n\nThe caretakers are settling your people into the city to the southeast. Go and speak to the leaders. Make sure they are safe.",
		"Speak to Jaluu the Generous, Kuru the Light-Hearted, Lucky Lin, and Matron Vi Vinh in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30632] = {
		"The Ruins of Guo-Lai",
		"According to Zhi the Harmonious, the mogu are moving into the Vale from the Ruins of Guo-Lai to the west.\n\nI sent Anji and Kun to investigate the situation, but they have not yet returned.\n\nI need a capable $c like you to go check on them.",
		"Speak to Anji Autumnlight at the Ruins of Guo-Lai in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30633] = {
		"Out with the Scouts",
		"We'd been briefed on mogu sightings in the Vale, but the situation is worse than we had anticipated.\n\nScouts are swarming all over the ruins to the northwest, gathering intel and stealing treasures.\n\nYour objective is clear - dispatch of any scouts you see. An army cannot move if we take out its eyes.",
		"Kill 8 Shao-Tien Precursor.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30634] = {
		"Barring Entry",
		"Lao Softfoot and I scouted up the ruins to the north.\n\nIt looks like the mogu are infiltrating the valley through a cave just up the hill, and already they are sending formidable reinforcements through.\n\nThere are too many enemies to take them head on, so you'll have to meet Lao Softfoot at the entrance to the ruins.\n\nHe'll help you sneak in under the cover of stealth. Then, plant this keg of explosives at the mouth of the cave.\n\nThe rest should take care of itself.",
		"Speak to Lao Softfoot at the entrance to Ruins Rise and follow him up the trail. Then, plant the Explosive Keg at the Ruins Rise Cave Entrance.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30635] = {
		"Killing the Quilen",
		"We've taken care of the scout problem for now, but there are still advance mogu forces inside the Guo-Lai Halls down the hill.\n\nUnfortunately, their vicious guard dogs are protecting their operations deeper in the ruins.\n\nGo and dispatch of their beasts. Be on your guard - they can be quite good at blending into their surroundings.",
		"Kill 9 Stone Guardians.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30636] = {
		"Stones of Power",
		"Many thousands of years ago, the rulers of the Vale sought energy from a powerful crystal known as Revelite.\n\nWith this substance, they were able to power cities, factories, and engines of war.\n\nZhi the Harmonious has asked us to collect some crystals and bring them back to the city.\n\nKeep an eye out for them while you are in the ruins.",
		"Collect 7 Revelite Crystals.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30637] = {
		"The Guo-Lai Halls",
		"As you pass by the great door, you hear sounds from deep inside.\n\nAnji mentioned that advance mogu scouts had been sighted in this area. Perhaps they made their way down to the depths below.\n\nYour senses tingling, you decide to investigate.",
		"Investigate the mogu presence in the Guo-Lai Halls.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30638] = {
		"Leaving an Opening",
		"This is serious.\n\nKun and I will keep an eye on things here, but you should go to the Golden Pagoda.\n\nGo, swiftly!",
		"Speak to Leven Dawnblade at the Golden Pagoda in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30639] = {
		"The Secrets of Guo-Lai",
		"I just received information from a guard stationed near the Ruins of Guo-Lai that the Shado-Tien leader entered the halls, killing two of my men in the process. They're intent on something inside. We need to stop them.\n\nHe Softfoot has already followed them in. He should be waiting for you at the entrance to the western chambers.\n\nMove quickly, $n. I don't like the thought that the mogu may be a step ahead of us.",
		"Meet with He Softfoot in the Guo-Lai Halls and uncover the mogu's purpose in the western chamber.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30640] = {
		"Battle Spear of the Thunder King",
		"I have received some troubling news, $n.\n\nThe mogu are plotting to steal three artifacts of power from the Vale.\n\nWe must retrieve the artifacts immediately and hide them for safekeeping.\n\nThe first artifact is the Battle Spear of the Thunder King.\n\nUpon emperor Lei Shen's death, the spear was placed in an ancient shrine to the northwest.\n\nBring the spear back to me.",
		"Retrieve the Battle Spear of the Thunder King.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30641] = {
		"Battle Helm of the Thunder King",
		"The second artifact of power is the Battle Helm of the Thunder King.\n\nEmperor Lei Shen wore the helm into every battle. It became so well-known that his enemies would flee at the mere sight of it.\n\nWhen the Emperor died, they placed the helm in the very bottom of the Guo-Lai Halls to the west, surrounded by thousands of terracotta soldiers.\n\nThus, they could look upon their leader and follow him into death.",
		"Retrieve the Battle Helm of the Thunder King.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30642] = {
		"Battle Axe of the Thunder King",
		"The final artifact is the Thunder King's axe.\n\nLei Shen charged into battle with his spear in one hand, and his axe in the other.\n\nIt is said that he could throw his axe with brutal accuracy, and when it hit its target, it made a sound like crashing thunder.\n\nAfter his death, the axe was placed in a ceremonial chamber to the southwest.\n\nNeedless to say, we must not let it fall into the mogu's hands.",
		"Retrieve the Battle Axe of the Thunder King.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30643] = {
		"The Mogu's Message",
		"The battle against the mogu rages fiercely with neither side giving quarter.\n\nWe cannot hold our position forever. Something must be done to strike a blow at the mogu, a blow from which they cannot recover.\n\nGo check in with Zhi the Harmonious at The Silent Sanctuary. I wish to hear his thoughts on this matter.",
		"Speak to Zhi the Harmonious at The Silent Sanctuary in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30644] = {
		"What Comes to Pass",
		"You had better report back to the Golden Pagoda immediately.",
		"Speak to Sun Tenderheart at the Golden Pagoda in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30645] = {
		"The Might of Three",
		"This is it, $n. This is the end.\n\nIf we don't drive the mogu from the valley, they will seize the remnants of their ancient power and use it to break Pandaria to their will.\n\nBut our forces are few, and tired, and small. We bleed, while their warriors are made of stone.\n\n$n, although all odds are against us, still I must ask you to go and help our forces slay the mogu invaders.\n\nI have prayed to the Celestials, begging their aid. I can only hope that they answer our call.",
		"Slay 100 mogu invaders at the Summer Fields in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30646] = {
		"The Final Power",
		"I never thought it would come to this!\n\nLeven went to face Warlord Zhao-Jin the Bloodletter at the top of the palace steps, but our reinforcements cannot get through!\n\nWe are the only ones who stand between him and the Vale's greatest... and most deadly... powers.\n\nPlease, $n, you must find a way to stop him!",
		"Kill Warlord Zhao-Jin the Bloodletter.",
		"Zhao-Jin the Bloodletter",
		"The leader of the Shao-Tien mogu.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30649] = {
		"The Shrine of Two Moons",
		"Look at this creature, traveler. Only moments after we arrived, this mogu assassin attacked with no warning.\n\nHis blade was intended for the leader of the Golden Lotus. It is very lucky indeed that we were here to stop the attack.\n\nSeeing this attempt on Zhi's life, I fear for the safety of those who have already entered the valley.\n\nThe caretakers are settling your people into the city to the northeast. Go and speak to the leaders. Make sure they are safe.",
		"Speak to Jaluu the Generous, Mokimo the Strong, Elder Liao, and Madam Vee Luo in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
	[30654] = {
		"The Guo-Lai Halls",
		"The mogu are up to something, I can feel it.\n\nThey've been sending scouts down into the Guo-Lai Halls.\n\nAccording to the caretakers, the Halls are home to ancient treasures of emperors past. Not only riches, but artifacts of great power.\n\nWe must prevent the mogu from accessing these treasures! Go down the ramp to the northwest and stop them!",
		"Investigate the mogu presence in the Guo-Lai Halls.",
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil,
		nil
	},
